01039 int cmdnfs_sattr2(
01040       cmdnfs_encodetype_t     encodeflag,
01041       int   argc,     char ** argv,
01042       int   indent,   FILE *  out_stream,
01043       caddr_t     p_nfs_struct
01044     )
01045 {
01046  
01047   sattr2 * p_sattr2 = (  sattr2 *) p_nfs_struct ;
01048 
01049   char * next_str = NULL;
01050   char * attrib_str;
01051   char * value_str;
01052 
01053     int mode, userid, groupid, rc;
01054   time_t  a_sec,m_sec;
01055   int     a_usec, m_usec;
01056   unsigned long long size;
01057   char * usec_str;
01058   char * time_str;
01059       
01060   char tmp_buff[1024];
01061         
01062   /* sanity check */
01063   if ( p_sattr2 == NULL ) return FALSE;
01064   
01065   switch ( encodeflag )
01066   {
01067     case CMDNFS_ENCODE:
01068       
01069 
01070       /* inits structure */
01071       
01072       p_sattr2->mode = (unsigned int)-1;
01073       p_sattr2->uid= (unsigned int)-1;
01074           p_sattr2->gid= (unsigned int)-1;
01075           p_sattr2->size= (unsigned int)-1;
01076           p_sattr2->atime.seconds= (unsigned int)-1;
01077           p_sattr2->atime.useconds= (unsigned int)-1;
01078           p_sattr2->mtime.seconds= (unsigned int)-1;
01079           p_sattr2->mtime.useconds= (unsigned int)-1;
01080             
01081       if ( argc == 0 ) return TRUE;
01082       
01083       /* at this point it must not be more than one string */
01084       if (argc != 1) return FALSE;
01085       
01086       /* the attributes are:
01087        * mode, uid, gid, size, atime, mtime
01088        */
01089       strncpy( tmp_buff, argv[0], 1024 );
01090           
01091       attrib_str = strtok_r(tmp_buff,",",&next_str);
01092       
01093       if ( attrib_str == NULL )
01094       {
01095 #ifdef _DEBUG_NFS_SHELL
01096         printf( "Unexpected parsing error.\n");
01097 #endif
01098         return FALSE;
01099       }
01100       
01101       while ( attrib_str != NULL )
01102       {
01103         
01104         /* retrieving attribute name and value */
01105         attrib_str = strtok_r( attrib_str,"=",&value_str );
01106         
01107         if ( (attrib_str == NULL) || (value_str == NULL) )
01108         {
01109   #ifdef _DEBUG_NFS_SHELL
01110           printf( "Syntax error for sattr2.\nExpected syntax: <attr>=<value>,<attr>=<value>,...\n");
01111   #endif
01112           return FALSE;
01113         }
01114 
01115 #ifdef _DEBUG_NFS_SHELL
01116         printf( "Attribute: \"%s\", Value: \"%s\"\n",attrib_str,value_str);
01117 #endif
01118         
01119         if (!strcasecmp( attrib_str, "mode" ))
01120         {
01121           mode = atomode( value_str );
01122           if (mode < 0) return FALSE;
01123           p_sattr2->mode = (unsigned int) mode;
01124 #ifdef _DEBUG_NFS_SHELL      
01125           printf ("  mode = 0%o\n",p_sattr2->mode );
01126 #endif
01127         }
01128         else if (!strcasecmp( attrib_str, "uid" ))
01129         {
01130           userid = my_atoi( value_str );
01131           if (userid < 0) return FALSE; 
01132           p_sattr2->uid = (unsigned int) userid;
01133 #ifdef _DEBUG_NFS_SHELL      
01134           printf ("  uid = %u\n",p_sattr2->uid );
01135 #endif
01136         }
01137         else if (!strcasecmp( attrib_str, "gid" ))
01138         {
01139           groupid = my_atoi( value_str );
01140           if (groupid < 0) return FALSE;
01141           p_sattr2->gid = (unsigned int) groupid;
01142 #ifdef _DEBUG_NFS_SHELL      
01143           printf ("  gid = %u\n",p_sattr2->gid );
01144 #endif
01145         }
01146         else if (!strcasecmp( attrib_str, "size" ))
01147         {
01148           rc = ato64( value_str, &size );
01149           if ( rc ) return FALSE;
01150           if ( size > ( unsigned long long ) UINT_MAX ) return FALSE;
01151           p_sattr2->size = (unsigned int) size;
01152 #ifdef _DEBUG_NFS_SHELL
01153           printf ("  size = %u\n",p_sattr2->size );
01154 #endif
01155         }
01156         else if (!strcasecmp( attrib_str, "atime" ))
01157         {
01158           time_str = strtok_r(value_str,".",&usec_str);
01159 
01160           a_sec = atotime( time_str );
01161           if ( a_sec == ((time_t)-1)) return FALSE;
01162 
01163           if ( usec_str == NULL )
01164           {
01165             a_usec = 0;
01166           }
01167           else
01168           {
01169             a_usec = my_atoi( usec_str );
01170             /* 1 million is authorized and is interpreted by server as a "set to server time" */
01171             if ( (a_usec < 0) || (a_usec > 1000000) ) return FALSE;
01172           }
01173           p_sattr2->atime.seconds= (unsigned int)a_sec;
01174           p_sattr2->atime.useconds= (unsigned int)a_usec;          
01175           
01176 #ifdef _DEBUG_NFS_SHELL
01177           printf ("  atime = %u.%.6u\n", p_sattr2->atime.seconds,
01178                   p_sattr->atime.useconds );
01179 #endif
01180         }
01181         else if (!strcasecmp( attrib_str, "mtime" ))
01182         {
01183           time_str = strtok_r(value_str,".",&usec_str);
01184 
01185           m_sec = atotime( time_str );
01186           if ( m_sec == ((time_t)-1)) return FALSE;
01187 
01188           if ( usec_str == NULL )
01189           {
01190             m_usec = 0;
01191           }
01192           else
01193           {
01194             m_usec = my_atoi( usec_str );
01195             /* 1 million is authorized and is interpreted by server as a "set to server time" */
01196             if ( (m_usec < 0) || (m_usec > 1000000) ) return FALSE;
01197           }
01198           p_sattr2->mtime.seconds= (unsigned int)m_sec;
01199           p_sattr2->mtime.useconds= (unsigned int)m_usec;          
01200           
01201 #ifdef _DEBUG_NFS_SHELL
01202           printf ("  mtime = %u.%.6u\n", p_sattr2->mtime.seconds,
01203                   p_sattr->mtime.useconds );
01204 #endif
01205         }
01206         else
01207         {
01208   #ifdef _DEBUG_NFS_SHELL
01209           printf( "Syntax error for sattr2.\n<attr> must be one of the following: mode, uid, gid, size, atime, mtime.\n");
01210   #endif
01211           return FALSE;
01212         }
01213         
01214         attrib_str = next_str;
01215         
01216         next_str = NULL; /* paranoid setting */
01217         value_str = NULL; /* paranoid setting */
01218         
01219         if ( attrib_str != NULL )
01220           attrib_str = strtok_r(attrib_str,",",&next_str);
01221         
01222       }
01223       
01224       return TRUE;
01225       
01226     case CMDNFS_FREE:
01227       /* nothing to do */
01228       return TRUE;
01229       break;
01230       
01231     case CMDNFS_DECODE:
01232       /* never decoded */
01233     default:
01234       return FALSE;
01235   } 
01236

01662 /* interprets a list of attributes separated with a colon :
01663  * mode=0755,uid=...,gid=...,etc...
01664  */
01665 int cmdnfs_sattr3(
01666       cmdnfs_encodetype_t     encodeflag,
01667       int   argc,     char ** argv,
01668       int   indent,   FILE *  out_stream,
01669       caddr_t     p_nfs_struct
01670     )
01671 {
01672   sattr3 * p_sattr = ( sattr3 *) p_nfs_struct ;
01673   char * next_str = NULL;
01674   char * attrib_str;
01675   char * value_str;
01676   
01677   int mode, userid, groupid, rc;
01678   time_t  a_sec,m_sec;
01679   int     a_nsec, m_nsec;
01680   unsigned long long size;
01681   char * nsec_str;
01682   char * time_str;
01683   char tmp_buff[1024];
01684   
01685   /* sanity check */
01686   if ( p_sattr == NULL ) return FALSE;
01687   
01688   switch ( encodeflag )
01689   {
01690     case CMDNFS_ENCODE:
01691       
01692       /* inits structure */
01693       memset( (caddr_t)p_sattr, 0, sizeof( sattr3 ) );
01694       
01695       p_sattr->mode.set_it = FALSE;
01696       p_sattr->uid.set_it = FALSE;
01697       p_sattr->gid.set_it = FALSE;
01698       p_sattr->size.set_it = FALSE;
01699       p_sattr->atime.set_it = DONT_CHANGE;
01700       p_sattr->mtime.set_it = DONT_CHANGE;
01701         
01702       if ( argc == 0 ) return TRUE;
01703       
01704       /* at this point it must not be more than one string */
01705       if (argc != 1) return FALSE;
01706       
01707       /* the attributes are:
01708        * mode, uid, gid, size, atime, mtime
01709        */
01710       strncpy( tmp_buff, argv[0], 1024 );
01711           
01712       attrib_str = strtok_r(tmp_buff,",",&next_str);
01713       
01714       if ( attrib_str == NULL )
01715       {
01716 #ifdef _DEBUG_NFS_SHELL
01717         printf( "Unexpected parsing error.\n");
01718 #endif
01719         return FALSE;
01720       }
01721       
01722       while ( attrib_str != NULL )
01723       {
01724         
01725         /* retrieving attribute value */
01726         attrib_str = strtok_r( attrib_str,"=",&value_str );
01727         
01728         if ( (attrib_str == NULL) || (value_str == NULL) )
01729         {
01730   #ifdef _DEBUG_NFS_SHELL
01731           printf( "Syntax error for sattr3.\nExpected syntax: <attr>=<value>,<attr>=<value>,...\n");
01732   #endif
01733           return FALSE;
01734         }
01735 
01736 #ifdef _DEBUG_NFS_SHELL
01737         printf( "Attribute: \"%s\", Value: \"%s\"\n",attrib_str,value_str);
01738 #endif
01739         
01740         if (!strcasecmp( attrib_str, "mode" ))
01741         {
01742           mode = atomode( value_str );
01743           if (mode < 0) return FALSE;          
01744           p_sattr->mode.set_it = TRUE;
01745           p_sattr->mode.set_mode3_u.mode = (unsigned int) mode;
01746 #ifdef _DEBUG_NFS_SHELL      
01747           printf ("  mode = 0%o\n",p_sattr->mode.set_mode3_u.mode);
01748 #endif
01749         }
01750         else if (!strcasecmp( attrib_str, "uid" ))
01751         {
01752           userid = my_atoi( value_str );
01753           if (userid < 0) return FALSE;          
01754           p_sattr->uid.set_it = TRUE;
01755           p_sattr->uid.set_uid3_u.uid = (unsigned int) userid;
01756 #ifdef _DEBUG_NFS_SHELL      
01757           printf ("  uid = %u\n",p_sattr->uid.set_uid3_u.uid);
01758 #endif
01759         }
01760         else if (!strcasecmp( attrib_str, "gid" ))
01761         {
01762           groupid = my_atoi( value_str );
01763           if (groupid < 0) return FALSE;
01764           p_sattr->gid.set_it = TRUE;
01765           p_sattr->gid.set_gid3_u.gid = (unsigned int) groupid;
01766 #ifdef _DEBUG_NFS_SHELL      
01767           printf ("  gid = %u\n",p_sattr->gid.set_gid3_u.gid);
01768 #endif
01769         }
01770         else if (!strcasecmp( attrib_str, "size" ))
01771         {
01772           rc = ato64( value_str, &size );
01773           if ( rc ) return FALSE;      
01774           p_sattr->size.set_it = TRUE;
01775           p_sattr->size.set_size3_u.size = (size3) size;
01776 #ifdef _DEBUG_NFS_SHELL
01777           printf ("  size = %llu\n",p_sattr->size.set_size3_u.size);
01778 #endif
01779         }
01780         else if (!strcasecmp( attrib_str, "atime" ))
01781         {
01782           time_str = strtok_r(value_str,".",&nsec_str);
01783 
01784           a_sec = atotime( time_str );
01785           if ( a_sec == ((time_t)-1)) return FALSE;
01786 
01787           if ( nsec_str == NULL )
01788           {
01789             a_nsec = 0;
01790           }
01791           else
01792           {
01793             a_nsec = my_atoi( nsec_str );
01794             if ( (a_nsec < 0) || (a_nsec > 999999999) ) return FALSE;
01795           }
01796           
01797           p_sattr->atime.set_it = SET_TO_CLIENT_TIME;
01798           p_sattr->atime.set_atime_u.atime.seconds = a_sec;
01799           p_sattr->atime.set_atime_u.atime.nseconds = a_nsec;
01800           
01801 #ifdef _DEBUG_NFS_SHELL
01802           printf ("  atime = %u.%.9u\n", p_sattr->atime.set_atime_u.atime.seconds,
01803                   p_sattr->atime.set_atime_u.atime.nseconds );
01804 #endif
01805         }
01806         else if (!strcasecmp( attrib_str, "mtime" ))
01807         {
01808           time_str = strtok_r(value_str,".",&nsec_str);
01809 
01810           m_sec = atotime( time_str );
01811           if ( m_sec == ((time_t)-1)) return FALSE;
01812 
01813           if ( nsec_str == NULL )
01814           {
01815             m_nsec = 0;
01816           }
01817           else
01818           {
01819             m_nsec = my_atoi( nsec_str );
01820             if ( (m_nsec < 0) || (m_nsec > 999999999) ) return FALSE;
01821           }
01822           
01823           p_sattr->mtime.set_it = SET_TO_CLIENT_TIME;
01824           p_sattr->mtime.set_mtime_u.mtime.seconds = m_sec;
01825           p_sattr->mtime.set_mtime_u.mtime.nseconds = m_nsec;
01826 #ifdef _DEBUG_NFS_SHELL
01827           printf ("  mtime = %u.%.9u\n", p_sattr->mtime.set_mtime_u.mtime.seconds,
01828                   p_sattr->mtime.set_mtime_u.mtime.nseconds );
01829 #endif
01830         }
01831         else
01832         {
01833   #ifdef _DEBUG_NFS_SHELL
01834           printf( "Syntax error for sattr3.\n<attr> must be one of the following: mode, uid, gid, size, atime, mtime.\n");
01835   #endif
01836           return FALSE;
01837         }
01838         
01839         attrib_str = next_str;
01840         
01841         next_str = NULL; /* paranoid setting */
01842         value_str = NULL; /* paranoid setting */
01843         
01844         if ( attrib_str != NULL )
01845           attrib_str = strtok_r(attrib_str,",",&next_str);
01846 
01847       }
01848       
01849       
01850       
01851       return TRUE;
01852       break;
01853       
01854     case CMDNFS_FREE:      
01855       /* nothing to do */      
01856       return TRUE;      
01857       break;
01858       
01859     case CMDNFS_DECODE:
01860       /* never decoded */
01861     default:
01862       return FALSE;
01863   }
01864 
01865 } /* cmdnfs_sattr3 */

02139 static int cmdnfs_verf3(
02140       cmdnfs_encodetype_t     encodeflag,
02141       int   argc,     char ** argv,
02142       int   indent,   FILE *  out_stream,
02143       caddr_t     p_nfs_struct,
02144       char * verfname /* name to be printed for the verifier (DECODE mode only) */
02145     )
02146 {
02147   /* pointer to an opaque buff */
02148   caddr_t p_verf = p_nfs_struct ;
02149   
02150   char * str_verf;
02151   char str_printverf[ 17 ];
02152   int rc;
02153   
02154   /* sanity check */
02155   if ( p_verf == NULL ) return FALSE;
02156   
02157   switch ( encodeflag )
02158   {
02159     case CMDNFS_ENCODE:
02160       
02161       if ( argc != 1 )  return FALSE;
02162       
02163       str_verf = argv[0];
02164       
02165       memset( p_verf, 0, 8 );
02166       
02167       rc = sscanmem( p_verf, 8, str_verf );
02168       
02169 #ifdef _DEBUG_NFS_SHELL
02170         fprintf(stderr,"verf = \"%s\"\n",str_verf);
02171         fprintf(stderr,"-> %d bytes read.\n",rc);
02172         fprintf(stderr,"buffer=%02X.%02X.%02X.%02X.%02X.%02X.%02X.%02X\n",
02173                        p_verf[0],p_verf[1],p_verf[2],p_verf[3],
02174                        p_verf[4],p_verf[5],p_verf[6],p_verf[7] );
02175         
02176 #endif
02177               
02178       /* we must have read at least the verf size */
02179       if ( rc < 0 ) return FALSE;
02180       
02181       return TRUE;
02182       
02183       break;
02184     case CMDNFS_DECODE:
02185       
02186       if ( snprintmem( str_printverf, 17, p_verf , 8 )
02187            < 0 )
02188       {
02189         return FALSE;
02190       }
02191           
02192       fprintf(out_stream, "%*s%s = %s\n",indent, " ", verfname, str_printverf);
02193       
02194       return TRUE;      
02195       break;
02196       
02197     case CMDNFS_FREE:
02198       /* nothing to do */
02199       return TRUE;      
02200       break;
02201       
02202     default:
02203       return FALSE;
02204   }
02205 }

02832 int cmdnfs_ACCESS3args(
02833       cmdnfs_encodetype_t     encodeflag,
02834       int   argc,     char ** argv,
02835       int   indent,   FILE *  out_stream,
02836       caddr_t     p_nfs_struct    
02837     )
02838 {
02839   ACCESS3args * p_access3args = (  ACCESS3args *) p_nfs_struct ;
02840 
02841   char * str_access;
02842   /* sanity check */
02843   if ( p_access3args == NULL ) return FALSE;
02844   
02845   switch ( encodeflag )
02846   {
02847     case CMDNFS_ENCODE:
02848       
02849       if ( argc != 2 ) return FALSE;
02850       
02851       if ( cmdnfs_fhandle3( CMDNFS_ENCODE, 1, argv , 0, NULL,
02852                             (caddr_t) &(p_access3args->object) ) == FALSE )
02853       {
02854         return FALSE;
02855       }
02856       
02857       /* access 2e arg: R(ead) L(ookup) M(odify) E(xtend) D(elete) (e)X(ecute) */
02858       /* convert a "RLMEDX" string to an NFS access mask. */
02859       
02860       p_access3args->access = 0;
02861       
02862       str_access = argv[1];
02863       while ( str_access[0] != '\0' )
02864       {
02865         if ( (str_access[0] == 'r') || (str_access[0] == 'R') )
02866           p_access3args->access |= ACCESS3_READ;
02867         else if ( (str_access[0] == 'l') || (str_access[0] == 'L') )
02868           p_access3args->access |= ACCESS3_LOOKUP;
02869         else if ( (str_access[0] == 'm') || (str_access[0] == 'M') )
02870           p_access3args->access |= ACCESS3_MODIFY;
02871         else if ( (str_access[0] == 'e') || (str_access[0] == 'E') )
02872           p_access3args->access |= ACCESS3_EXTEND;
02873         else if ( (str_access[0] == 'd') || (str_access[0] == 'D') )
02874           p_access3args->access |= ACCESS3_DELETE;
02875         else if ( (str_access[0] == 'x') || (str_access[0] == 'X') )
02876           p_access3args->access |= ACCESS3_EXECUTE;
02877         else
02878         {
02879 #ifdef _DEBUG_NFS_SHELL
02880           fprintf(stderr,"access flag error: unknown flag \"%c\".\n",str_access[0]);
02881 #endif
02882           return FALSE;
02883         }
02884         
02885         str_access ++;
02886       }
02887             
02888       return TRUE;
02889       
02890     case CMDNFS_FREE:
02891       cmdnfs_fhandle3( CMDNFS_FREE, 0, NULL , 0, NULL,
02892                             (caddr_t) &(p_access3args->object) );
02893       return TRUE;
02894       break;
02895       
02896     case CMDNFS_DECODE:
02897       /* never decoded */
02898     default:
02899       return FALSE;
02900   } 
02901 }

02992 int cmdnfs_CREATE3args(
02993       cmdnfs_encodetype_t     encodeflag,
02994       int   argc,     char ** argv,
02995       int   indent,   FILE *  out_stream,
02996       caddr_t     p_nfs_struct    
02997     )
02998 {
02999   CREATE3args * p_CREATE3args = (  CREATE3args *) p_nfs_struct ;
03000   char * str_mode;
03001   
03002   /* sanity check */
03003   if ( p_CREATE3args == NULL ) return FALSE;
03004   
03005   switch ( encodeflag )
03006   {
03007     case CMDNFS_ENCODE:
03008       
03009       if ( (argc != 3) && (argc != 4) ) return FALSE;
03010       
03011       /* The first two args */
03012       if ( cmdnfs_diropargs3( CMDNFS_ENCODE, 2, argv , 0, NULL,
03013                             (caddr_t) &(p_CREATE3args->where) ) == FALSE )
03014       {
03015         return FALSE;
03016       }
03017       
03018       /* CREATE 3e arg: UNCHECKED, GUARDED or EXCLUSIVE */
03019       
03020       str_mode = argv[2];
03021       if (!strcasecmp( str_mode, "UNCHECKED" ))
03022         p_CREATE3args->how.mode = UNCHECKED;
03023       else if (!strcasecmp( str_mode, "GUARDED" ))
03024         p_CREATE3args->how.mode = GUARDED;
03025       else if (!strcasecmp( str_mode, "EXCLUSIVE" ))
03026         p_CREATE3args->how.mode = EXCLUSIVE;
03027       else
03028         return FALSE;
03029       
03030       /* CREATE 4th arg: sattr3 list or a create verifier */
03031       
03032       switch( p_CREATE3args->how.mode )
03033       {
03034         case UNCHECKED:
03035         case GUARDED:
03036           
03037           /* The optional 4th arg is a sattr3 list */
03038           if ( cmdnfs_sattr3( CMDNFS_ENCODE, argc -3, argv + 3, 0, NULL,
03039                              (caddr_t)&(p_CREATE3args->how.createhow3_u.obj_attributes))
03040                              == FALSE )
03041           {
03042             return FALSE;
03043           }
03044           
03045           break;
03046         case EXCLUSIVE:
03047           
03048           /* The mandatory 4rd arg is a create verifier*/
03049           if ( cmdnfs_verf3( CMDNFS_ENCODE, argc - 3, argv + 3, 0, NULL,
03050                            (caddr_t)&(p_CREATE3args->how.createhow3_u.verf),
03051                             NULL ) == FALSE )
03052           {
03053             return FALSE;
03054           }
03055           
03056           break;
03057       }
03058        
03059       return TRUE;
03060       
03061     case CMDNFS_FREE:
03062       
03063       cmdnfs_diropargs3( CMDNFS_FREE, 0, NULL , 0, NULL,
03064                             (caddr_t) &(p_CREATE3args->where) );
03065       
03066       switch( p_CREATE3args->how.mode )
03067       {
03068         case UNCHECKED:
03069         case GUARDED:
03070         cmdnfs_sattr3( CMDNFS_FREE, 0, NULL , 0, NULL,
03071                       (caddr_t) &(p_CREATE3args->how.createhow3_u.obj_attributes) );
03072           break;
03073         
03074         case EXCLUSIVE:
03075           cmdnfs_verf3( CMDNFS_FREE, 0, NULL , 0, NULL,
03076                       (caddr_t) &(p_CREATE3args->how.createhow3_u.verf), NULL );
03077         break;
03078       }
03079       
03080       return TRUE;
03081       break;
03082       
03083     case CMDNFS_DECODE:
03084       /* never decoded */
03085     default:
03086       return FALSE;
03087   } 
03088 }

03562 int cmdnfs_sattrguard3(
03563       cmdnfs_encodetype_t     encodeflag,
03564       int   argc,     char ** argv,
03565       int   indent,   FILE *  out_stream,
03566       caddr_t     p_nfs_struct
03567     )
03568 {
03569   sattrguard3 * p_sattr = ( sattrguard3 *) p_nfs_struct ;
03570   
03571   time_t  c_sec;
03572   int     c_nsec;
03573   char * nsec_str;
03574   char * time_str;
03575     
03576   /* sanity check */
03577   if ( p_sattr == NULL ) return FALSE;
03578   
03579   switch ( encodeflag )
03580   {
03581     case CMDNFS_ENCODE:
03582       
03583       /* inits structure */
03584       memset( (caddr_t)p_sattr, 0, sizeof( sattrguard3 ) );
03585         
03586       if ( argc == 0 )
03587       {
03588         /* empty structure */
03589         p_sattr->check = FALSE;
03590         return TRUE;
03591       }
03592       
03593       /* at this point it must not be more than one string */
03594       if (argc != 1) return FALSE;
03595       
03596       time_str = strtok_r(argv[0],".",&nsec_str);
03597 
03598       c_sec = atotime( time_str );
03599       if ( c_sec == ((time_t)-1)) return FALSE;
03600 
03601       if ( nsec_str == NULL )
03602       {
03603         c_nsec = 0;
03604       }
03605       else
03606       {
03607         c_nsec = my_atoi( nsec_str );
03608         if ( (c_nsec < 0) || (c_nsec > 999999999) ) return FALSE;
03609       }
03610 
03611       p_sattr->check = TRUE;
03612       p_sattr->sattrguard3_u.obj_ctime.seconds = c_sec;
03613       p_sattr->sattrguard3_u.obj_ctime.nseconds = c_nsec;
03614 
03615 #ifdef _DEBUG_NFS_SHELL
03616       printf ("ctime check = %u.%.9u\n", p_sattr->sattrguard3_u.obj_ctime.seconds,
03617               p_sattr->sattrguard3_u.obj_ctime.nseconds );
03618 #endif
03619       
03620       return TRUE;
03621       break;
03622     case CMDNFS_FREE:      
03623       /* nothing to do */      
03624       return TRUE;      
03625       break;
03626       
03627     case CMDNFS_DECODE:
03628       /* never decoded */
03629     default:
03630       return FALSE;
03631   }
03632 
03633 } /* cmdnfs_sattrguard3 */
